\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. E. flavum} Desf.,{\i  Fl. Atl.} {\b 1}: 165 (1798) ({\i E. fontanesii} DC.). Erect or ascending biennial or perennial 20-80 cm, with 1 or usually several flowering stems. Basal leaves 40-150 × 8-30 mm, narrowly obovate to oblanceolate, with soft, appressed setae; cauline leaves very narrowly elliptical. Inflorescence spike-like. Calyx 5-8 mm. Corolla 13-16 mm, very narrowly infundibuliform, flesh-pink, with 5 long-exserted stamens; filaments red.{\i  Screes and mountain pastures; calcicole. S., C. & E. Spain.} Hs.
