\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 9. E. russicum} J. F. Gmelin, {\i Syst. Nat.}{\b  2}: 323 (1791) ({\i E. rubrum} Jacq., non Forskal). Erect, hispid biennial 25-50 cm, with 1 to several flowering stems. Basal and cauline leaves 55-100 × 4-10 mm, lanceolate to narrowly elliptical, attenuate at the base, with soft, appressed setae. Inflorescence spike-like. Calyx 5-6 mm. Corolla 9-12 mm, more or less infundibuliform, dark red, with 4-5 long-exserted stamens; filaments red. 2n = 24.{\i  Meadows and uncultivated slopes, scrub. E.C. & S.E. Europe, extending northwards to} c. 55°{\i  N. in C. Russia.} Al Au Bu Cz Hu Ju Po Rm Rs (C, W, K, E).
