\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 10. E. vulgare} L., {\i Sp. Pl.} 139 (1753). Erect, hispid biennial (or sometimes perennial ?) 20-90 cm, with 1 to several flowering stems. Leaves with rather soft, appressed setae; the basal and lower cauline 50-150 × 10-20 mm, elliptical to lanceolate, attenuate and petiolate at base; the upper narrowly lanceolate, sessile. Inflorescence more or less spike-like to paniculate. Calyx 5-7 mm. Corolla 10-19 mm, blue to bluish-violet, with 4-5 long-exserted stamens. 2n = 16, 32. {\i Almost throughout Europe.} All except Az Bl Fa Is Rs (N) Sb; casual in some of these.
