\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 11. E. plantagineum} L., {\i Mantissa Alt.} 202 (1771) ({\i E. lycopsis} L. pro parte,{\i  E. maritimum} Willd.). Erect, softly hairy, annual or biennial 20-60 cm, with 1 to many flowering stems. Basal leaves 50-140 × c. 15 mm, ovate, with prominent lateral veins and soft appressed setae; cauline leaves oblong to lanceolate the uppermost more or less cordate at the base. Inflorescence usually branched. Calyx 7-10 mm at anthesis, up to 15 mm in fruit. Corolla 18-30 mm, infundibuliform, blue becoming pink through purple, hairy on veins and margins only, usually with 2 exserted stamens. 2n = 16.{\i  Roadsides, fields and sandy areas near the sea. S. & W. Europe, northwards to S.W. England; an occasional casual elsewhere.} Al Az Bl Br Bu Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Lu Rs (C, K) Sa Si Tu.
